Compute mu
=================================

Example  (LJ, T = 10, rho = 0.7)
---------------------------------

Type make
make

Do an integral equation based on the PY closure
./muhs --py -T10 --rho=0.7 --drho=0.7 --lj -v --crtr=crtrpy.dat

Do an integral equation based on the HNC closure
./muhs --hnc -T10 --rho=0.7 --drho=0.7 --lj -v --crtr=crtrhnc.dat

Do an integral equation based on the self-consistent closure
  (quadratic closure)
./muhs -s-0.0852528 -T10 --rho=0.7 --drho=0.7 --lj -v --crtr=crtrsqr.dat

The parameter -0.0852528 is obtained from
./ieodfftw --lj -T10 --lamc --sqrs=1

Do an integral equation based on the explicit RDF,
  with the core part of the bridge function computed
  from the free energy calculation.

./muhs -T10 --rho=0.7 --lj -v \
  --gr=mc/mcdata/rdfT10rho0.7n256.dat \
  --pmf=mc/mcdata/pmfT10rho0.7n256.dat \
  --Brout=Brout1.dat --crtr=crtr1.dat

rab 0.6506
th  0.4418

Do an integral equation based on the explicit RDF,
  with the core part of the bridge function extrapolated
  by a polynomial.

./muhs -T10 --rho=0.7 --lj -v \
  --gr=mc/mcdata/rdfT10rho0.7n256.dat \
  --Brout=Brout2.dat --crtr=crtr2.dat

rab 0.6471
th  0.4412




